German E. Coli Probe Targets Luebeck Restaurant, Luebecker Says

-- B y   N a o m i   K r e s g e
-- 
2011-06-04T12:06:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-04/german-e-coli-probe-targets-luebeck-restaurant-luebecker-says.html
Authorities are investigating a
restaurant in Luebeck,  Germany , as a possible source of cases in
the European E. coli outbreak,  Luebecker Nachrichten  reported,
without saying where it got the information.  Seventeen people fell ill in mid-May after eating at the
restaurant in the northern coastal city, the newspaper said.
Investigators from the Robert Koch Institute and the  Federal
Institute for Risk Assessment  arrived in Luebeck yesterday, the
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Naomi Kresge in Zurich at 
 nkresge@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
